8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 804, L.D. 1229, “An Act to Create
10 Equity in Maine's Campaign Finance Laws Between Enrolled and Unenrolled Candidates”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Create Equity in Maine's Campaign Finance Laws'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 21-A MRSA §1015, sub-§3-A is enacted to read:
16 3-A. Modifications of limitations on contributions for general election candidates.
17 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, for purposes of contribution limits
18 under subsections 1 and 2-B:
19 A. For a candidate in a general election who was nominated by primary election, the
20 candidate may receive contributions from a source for purposes of the general election
21 aggregating up to twice the amount established for contribution limits in subsections 1
22 and 2-B, minus any contributions the source provided to the candidate for purposes of
23 the primary election; and
24 B. For a gubernatorial or legislative candidate in a general election who was nominated
25 by petition or through the replacement procedures in section 374-A, the candidate has
26 the same contribution limits as a candidate for the same office who was on the ballot
27 in the primary election.'
28 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
29 number to read consecutively.
30 SUMMARY
3311 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment provides that a candidate in a
3322 general election who was nominated by primary election may receive contributions from a
3333 source for the general election aggregating up to twice the amount established for
3344 contribution limits to candidates in support of the candidate's candidacy. This amount is
