315 reduced by any contributions made by that source to the candidate for the purposes of the
326 primary election. The amendment also provides that a gubernatorial or legislative
337 candidate in a general election who was nominated by petition or who was nominated as a
348 replacement nominee by a political committee for the general election has the same
359 contribution limits as a candidate for the same office who was on the ballot in the primary
460 election.
